# üìù Datalist Support Demo - Phase 2 HTML5 Enhancement

This demo showcases FormDown's new datalist support for autocomplete functionality.

## Explicit Datalist Declaration

You can define reusable datalist elements:

```formdown
@datalist[id="countries" options="Korea,Japan,China,USA,Canada,UK,Germany,France"]
@datalist[id="programming-languages" options="JavaScript,TypeScript,Python,Java,C#,Go,Rust"]
```

@datalist[id="countries" options="Korea,Japan,China,USA,Canada,UK,Germany,France"]
@datalist[id="programming-languages" options="JavaScript,TypeScript,Python,Java,C#,Go,Rust"]

## Using Datalist with Fields

### Explicit Reference (Recommended for Reusable Lists)

@country(Preferred Country): [text datalist="countries" autocomplete="country"]
@language(Primary Language): [text datalist="programming-languages"]

### Shorthand Syntax (Auto-Generated Datalist)

The shorthand syntax automatically creates datalist elements:

@city{Seoul,Tokyo,Beijing,New York,London,Paris}: [text autocomplete="address-level2"]
@framework{React,Vue,Angular,Svelte,Next.js}: [text]
@browser{Chrome,Firefox,Safari,Edge}: [text]

